    "instruction": "Using log.csv only, filter rows to timestamps between 1647849600 and 1647851400 inclusive. Then aggregate by cmdb_id and return a compact table (max 20 rows) with these columns: cmdb_id, total_rows_in_window (count of log rows), sum_log_error_count (sum of value where log_name == 'log.error_count'), sum_log_row_count (sum of value where log_name == 'log.row_count'), earliest_error_timestamp (minimum timestamp within window where log.error_count > 0, null if none), max_log_error_count (maximum log.error_count value in window). Order results by sum_log_error_count desc, then by sum_log_row_count desc, and limit to top 20 rows. Also include a single summary line with the number of distinct cmdb_id that had sum_log_error_count > 0 within the window."
